lass=3D" edan-search-results__content">
                          This example of the Unicon was given to the Museu=
m by one of its inventors, David J. Schlink (1931=E2=80=932010). Schlink an=
d Walter K. Schwarz received U.S.Patent No. 3,680,775 on 1 August 1972 for =
the Unicon. They assigned the patent to Schlink=E2=80=99s employer, The Peo=
ria Journal Star, Inc., of Peoria, Illinois. Under the name PJS Enterprises=
, the newspaper manufactured and sold the Unicon for $3.95 retail. Distribu=
tion soon was taken over by Unicon Enterprises of Peoria, which sold a late=
r version of the instrument, the Unicon II, as late as 1988. By this time, =
foreign travelers also were advised to take along electronic calculators fo=
r currency conversion.
                        </dd>
